&lt;h1&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Farmer’s Dog Veterinary Student Ambassador Program&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;About The Farmer’s Dog:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Farmer’s Dog (TFD) is on a mission to make dogs healthier and happier by feeding them&amp;nbsp;freshly prepared food, designed for long term health. Formulated by boarded veterinary&amp;nbsp;nutritionists from day one, we value the veterinary profession and seek to partner with the&amp;nbsp;veterinary community to advance the conversation around evidence-based nutrition and elevate&amp;nbsp;the standard of care for pets everywhere.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Student Ambassador Program Overview:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Farmer’s Dog is seeking motivated second- or third-year veterinary students to serve as&amp;nbsp;Student Ambassadors.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Farmer’s Dog Student Ambassador Program&lt;/strong&gt; offers second-or-third year veterinary students enrolled in AVMA -accredited veterinary programs the opportunity to build leadership skills, connect with industry experts, and represent TFD within their academic communities. Ambassadors participate in on-campus activities within their respective academic communities, support education around evidence-based nutrition, and provide feedback that help inform TFD’s initiatives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, students act as peer leaders and mentors, serving as a trusted resource for&amp;nbsp;classmates about TFD products and services while advancing pet care through thoughtful&amp;nbsp;conversations about canine nutrition.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;How You’ll Be Making an Impact&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a mentor and peer resource to your student community by representing TFD professionally and in alignment with TFD’s mission and values.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and participate in campus events, student organization meetings, and informational discussions related to veterinary nutrition.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organize or assist with on-campus educational events in consultation with TFD.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Share non-confidential feedback and insights from your student community to help TFD support the next generation of veterinarians.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What makes you a great fit?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Second or third year veterinary student in good academic standing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Currently enrolled in an AVMA-accredited veterinary program.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication and interpersonal skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated leadership and initiative through student organizations or professional roles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proactive, self-starter, who is capable of working independently with limited supervision.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enthusiasm for veterinary nutrition and advancing pet health.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to commit to the position for one school year, with an option to renew.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;What We Offer:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;$1,000 flat-rate payment per semester&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leadership opportunities and career development support from TFD veterinarians and industry leaders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Potential optional opportunities for travel to conferences, or other TFD held events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A discounted TFD subscription rate while serving as Ambassador&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
